Diuresis is an important mode of treatment for cardiovascular diseases, such as hypertension. It can increase the urinary volume and has a fewer side effect compared to others. Diuretics usually used as an independent drug or a combination with other drugs of the same mechanism of action in easing various conditions such as congestive heart failure, ascites, and pulmonary edema as well. Thus, few of the available diuretics cause adverse effects such as an imbalance of electrolytes, alterations in metabolic status, and some may impair the sexual function (
 Gupta and Neyses, 2005; 
 Morganti, 2005).
